# Storybook contracts

## Runtimes

- **Desktop web:** stories only under `packages/eskerra-ds-desktop` (not shared with mobile).
- **Mobile:** on-device and RN-Web share the **same** story files under `packages/eskerra-ds-mobile`.

## L2 — Design-system contract stories

- Location: `packages/eskerra-ds-*/**/__stories__/` (and `__stories__/reference/` for static galleries).
- **Interactive components:** mandatory variants (Default, Disabled where applicable, Loading, LongContent, focus/pressed, A11y); use **`play`** from `storybook/test` to assert behavior (e.g. disabled control does not fire handlers).
- **Static reference stories:** allowed for token palettes, typography specimens, icon inventories, surface references — tag `reference` / `docs-only`; place under `__stories__/reference/`; no `play` required. Must not replace contract coverage on interactive components.

## L3 — App sandbox stories

- Path: `apps/*/src/**/__sandbox__/*.stories.tsx`; tag **`sandbox`**; not in official docs publish set; **`play` not required**.

## Mobile-only behavior

- Stories that depend on Reanimated, gesture-handler, or other native-only behavior: tag **`native-only`** so the RN-Web test-runner can skip them; on-device Storybook must still cover them.

## Anti-patterns

- No “visual-only” excuse for **interactive** L2 components without `play` + a11y coverage.
- No product compositions (`EditorWorkspaceToolbar`, vault trees, …) as L2 contract stories — use L3 sandbox if needed.
